<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-61-0604 </DOCNO><TEXT>The radiological diagnosis and differential diagnosis of opportunisticinfections become more difficult due to the broad spectrum of possiblepathogenic organisms, pulmonary complications as part of the underlyingdisease and finally through possible side effects of therapy. An assignmentof these changes to certain radiographic patterns seems useful. In themajority of cases the radiography by itself cannot lead to the correctdiagnosis. (orig./GDG).</TEXT></DOC>